A man in his 40s was killed his Volkswagen Polo crash into a
truck on the R59 in Sasolburg. When paramedics arrived on the scene they found a fuming
truck on the side of the road while the car was found parked a short distance
away. ER24 said it is understood that the truck had burst into
flame upon crashing with the car and the driver was able to escape without
injury. “On closer inspection, medics found a man believed to be in
his 40s lying trapped inside the light motor vehicle.” The man had already succumbed to his numerous injuries, nothing
could be done for him, and he was declared dead. The details surrounding this incident are unknown, but local
authorities are conducting further investigations.